1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method for unsupervised domain adaptation using a Bayesian neural network to quantify prediction uncertainty of a classifier. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed method is evaluated on three popular benchmark datasets in computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel approach to address the issue of label distribution shift in unsupervised domain adaptation. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although the paper does not explicitly mention natural language processing, the proposed method could potentially be applied to domain adaptation in NLP tasks. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses a Bayesian neural network to quantify prediction uncertainty, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
